<div class="col five-sm clear">
<h2 id="section-top">Overview</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent94721453ba154e9190f95bdea7e3ab84">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Ross Community Hospital Photograph" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=2113" style="border-width:0px;"/>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong><strong>Coronavirus - please visit the Trust's website for updates regarding this - www.wyevalley.nhs.uk (there is a link on the right hand side of our main website page). </strong><br/><br/><strong>Do not visit hospital if you have symptoms of Coronavirus. </strong></strong></p>
<p>Our aim is to provide a quality of care that we would want for ourselves, our families and our friends.</p>
<p>Which means<br/>Right care, right place, right time...every time.</p>
<p>We provide ongoing medical care and rehabilitation to help you in your recovery when you have had treatment at The County Hospital or another hospital but are not well enough to go home.</p>
<p>To find out about the ward visiting times at Ross Community Hospital visit the Wye Valley NHS Trust website <a href="http://www.wyevalley.nhs.uk">www.wyevalley.nhs.uk</a> (Community Health  Services, Community Hospitals).</p>
<p><strong><strong>CLOSED - <strong>Ross Minor Injury Unit</strong> is closed throughout the winter period.  Please call NHS 111 if you need medical advice for minor illnesses or ailments.   </strong></strong></p>
<p> </p></div>
